
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-martini-pwe3-static-pw-status-02.txt'>
    <title>"Pseudowire Status for Static Pseudowires", Luca Martini, George Swallow, Matthew Bocci</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-martini-pwe3-static-pw-status-02.txt</link>
    <description>This document specifies a mechanism to signal Pseudowire (PW) status messages using an PW associated channel (ACh). Such a mechanism is suitable for use where no PW dynamic control plane exits, known as static PWs, or where a Terminating Provider Edge (T-PE) needs to send a PW status message directly to a far end T-PE. The mechanism allows PW OAM message mapping and PW redundancy to operate on static PWs.</description>
    <dc:date>2009-10-23T22:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
